Description:
Unique indoor/outdoor living.
Privately secluded on a pristinely landscaped corner block, this renovated three bedroom plus study home offers unique indoor/outdoor family living just moments to Coburg Hill Shopping Centre plus Newlands Primary and Coburg High Schools. A charming red brick exterior is matched within, open plan living flaunting a fully appointed smart kitchen and modern fireplace. The pergola covered alfresco area appreciates a picturesque garden backdrop and favourable aspect to inspire social gatherings. Meanwhile three double bedrooms presents built-in wardrobes, each with outlooks over tranquil gardens or the saltwater swimming pool and entertaining deck. There's also a light filled study with separate entry, split system air conditioner, remote 1.5 car garage, laundry and copious under house storage with cellar potential.
Insights: 1 Meadow Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Timeless Charm with Immediate Style and Future Excellence
In a family-focused neighbourhood with close proximity to the best of Coburg, this captivating Californian provides an instantly enjoyable lifestyle of comfort and versatility along with outstanding opportunities for those looking to further enhance and expand in the future (STCA). Beyond the picket-fenced garden and gorgeous triple-gabled facade, discover an impeccably-presented interior comprising three bedrooms (two large - both with built-in robes) and two full bathrooms. Add to this a wide central lounge with open fireplace, rear sunroom and kitchen/meals area with solid timber cabinetry, dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances. Other stand-out features include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, high ornate ceilings, lead-light windows and solid timber floors, plus a substantial backyard complete with undercover entertaining deck, large studio/home office and adjoining workshop/storeroom, ROW potential and gated side driveway for multiple off-street parking. Walking distance to Melville Road trams, local buses, Coburg West and St Fidelis primary schools, Zoned to Strathmore Secondary College, close to Coburg Station and shopping precinct as well as easy access to Citylink/Tullamarine Freeway.

Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Contemporary Base In Vibrant Locale
With trains, buses, trams, cafes, Coburg Market, schools and Coburg Leisure Centre a stroll away, this contemporary two bedroom residence brings reverse living design to a superbly connected position. It features a flowing first floor with a well appointed kitchen transitioning to a dining area and living zone linked by sliding glass door to a wide covered balcony. Generous stone countertops including a waterfall breakfast bar meet with plentiful white cabinetry and stainless steel kitchen appliances, ranging from a gas cooktop to an electric fan forced oven and dishwasher, in the fully equipped kitchen. Downstairs, two double bedrooms offer mirrored built-in robes and the fully tiled dual entry bathroom presents a bath, separate rainfall shower, toilet, stone topped vanity with raised basin and heat lamp. Extras include a small courtyard, concealed laundry, polished floorboards, high ceilings, heating and cooling units in bedrooms and living areas and off street parking right at the front door. Investors and aspiring residents can't help but see the appeal in leaving the car at home and exploring the local area or easily travelling to the city's heart in next to no time.

Description:
Luxurious Contemporary Living
This is your chance to purchase a beautiful family home in a prized neighbourhood only 7km from CBD and minutes from quality schools such as St Bernards and Coburg Primary schools. The home is also within walking distance of a Route 1 tram stop located 250 metres away and the Merri Creek nature walk. A short trip by car will take you to Sydney Road and Bell Street shopping and cafe precincts.
Perfectly positioned, this attractive renovated home will indulge its occupants with contemporary amenities, quality fixtures and fittings to ensure both practicality and aesthetics are not only met but also exceeded. Every inch of this home is pure bespoke design and not a penny spared!
An expansive entry hall with a vanity mirror, coat wardrobe, and shelves hidden behind imported glass frosted doors leads into a practical layout, providing multi-purpose versatility for zoned entertainment with two natural light-filled lounges - one in front, one with an adjoining dining area and a large modern kitchen. The large modern kitchen is a true celebration of high-end design, delivering granite benchtops, subway-tiled splashback, quality stainless steel appliances and plenty of storage options and space to cook up a storm!
Two master bedrooms - one with walk-in robes, the other with built-in robes - lead into sleek ensuites with double showers, whilst two additional bedrooms (one with walk-in robes, the other with built-in robes) share the family bathroom boasting a luxurious bathtub alongside a shower. A powder room is located next to the house's side entrance.
The stunning backyard, easy-to-maintain landscaping and entertainment space provide a relaxing place to entertain all year round. There is a dedicated storage room next to the backyard, and ample off-street car parking for up to 3 cars.
With not a thing to do, simply move in, unpack and enjoy for many years to come!
Highlights include:
*ducted heating, evaporative air conditioning, electric hot water system and central ducted vacuum
*whole house water filter, under-sink ambient and hot water filters
double-glazed windows throughout the house
*granite benchtops in the bathrooms, kitchen, and laundry room
an intercom and alarm system
*ample off-street car parking for up to 3 cars and storage/workshop/studio.
*sleek polished hardwood floors, quality fittings and fixtures throughout including LED downlights
*imported glass frosted doors offering attractive storage options
Land Size: 627sqm approx
House Size: 30sq inc workshop
Deposit: 10% of the purchase price
Settlement: 90/120 days
Chattels: All fixtures and fittings as inspected
Heating: Gas Ducted
Cooling: Evaporative Cooling
Deposit Terms: 10% of the purchase price
Rental Appraisal: $ $680 -$700 pw approx
Nearest Primary Schools: St Bernards and Coburg Primary schools
Nearest Secondary Schools: Antonine College, Mercy College and Coburg High School.
Nearest Public Transport: Tram, bus and train stations
Internal area
280m²

Description:
Retro Style Meets Cool Contemporary Flair
Enviably positioned in Coburg's exclusive Moreland Park precinct, this boutique villa (one of only five) presents a sensational low-maintenance lifestyle opportunity with its distinctive architecture, flexible floorplan and quality enhancements throughout. Every room filled with natural light, the home's on-trend interior comprises two generous bedrooms (both with large built-in robes), stylish central bathroom and separate WC. Add to this a spacious open-plan living/dining area flanked by floor-to-ceiling windows and further accentuated by high vaulted ceilings, plus a contemporary kitchen complete with tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances, Bosch dishwasher and ample cupboard space. Other stand-out features of the home include split-system heating and cooling, concealed laundry facilities, polished concrete floors throughout. Outside discover a sunny full-width courtyard with high fences for added privacy along with a designated off-street parking space. Walking distance to Nicholson Street trams, local parks and Merri Creek trails, close to primary and secondary schools, as well as easy access to Moreland Station, Sydney Road's renowned shops, cafes and restaurants.

Description:
Spacious And Central With Modern Appeal
Quietly located, yet within easy reach of the area's best amenities, this modern three bedroom, two bathroom home will excite families, professionals, starters and investors. Generously scaled, the open living domain is complemented by an alfresco deck, both serviced by an elegant stone topped kitchen boasting glass splashbacks, 900mm cooking appliances and dishwasher. Double bedrooms include two with WIRs, the third (BIRs) enjoying 270 degree views from a north facing balcony while a smart fully tiled bathroom on each floor delivers ultimate convenience. Two off street parking spaces comprise one at the front plus a carport at the rear (ROW) which otherwise doubles as a second outdoor entertaining area. There's also split system air conditioners in all main rooms, laundry with kitchenette, solar panels, good storage and a water tank. Steps to tennis and bowling clubs, it's also just a short distance from Coburg train station, schools plus Sydney Road shops, cafes and tram.

Description:
"Sweetwater"
Nestled in a coveted tree-lined street, "Sweetwater" is an elegant three bedroom Art Deco home zoned to Strathmore College. Instantly evoking positive impressions with features including leadlight, a gas coal fireplace, Deco ceiling details and polished floorboards, it offers adjoining formal living and dining rooms plus a kitchen/meals, open study and spacious family room. A gas cooktop, gas oven and Asko dishwasher harmonise with plentiful counter space and timber cabinetry in the fully equipped kitchen/meals, designed for easy meal preparation. To the rear is a two stage entertainer's deck with covered dining and relaxation areas. Showcasing a leadlight bay window with window seat, the main bedroom is complemented by two more double bedrooms with built-in robes. Featuring a wide stone topped vanity and shower, the tasteful bathroom is centrally positioned. Central heating and evaporative cooling have been installed for comfort, a big shed offers great storage space, there's a handy carport and schools, Shore Reserve, cafes, local shops and Melville Road trams are all within a stroll.

Description:
Quiet, spacious and peaceful with tree top views
Quiet, serene and meticulously well presented, this large one bedroom plus study apartment is the perfect entry point into Coburg - one of Melbourne's most sought after suburbs. Beautifully elevated for maximum light, security and stunning urban views of tree tops and heritage bluestone buildings, this represents an outstanding city edge lifestyle.
Features include a large undercover balcony, perfect for entertaining or watching the sunsets, modern bathroom with laundry facilities, large master bedroom with built in robes and balcony access, split system heating & cooling, gas cooking, granite benchtops, intercom access and parking space to be allocated in the AIR Building, currently offsite space is available. The standout for any apartment is space, with a floorplan that outstrips any modern building, ceiling heights that provide a warehouse feel, the volume is undeniably impressive.
This home is located within a 5 minute walk to the Route 19 tram on Sydney Rd which takes you into the city with absolute ease. With your own café, The Boot Factory at the base of the building for all your coffee and brunch needs. Stroll to Merri Creek, Coburg Leisure Centre, schools and shops are all close by for your convenience, making this an opportunity not to be missed!

Description:
Contemporary, convenient city living.
Sale By Set Date Closing Monday 30th of September at 5pm
Modern, carefree living is assured with this spacious and serene residence showcasing three bedrooms plus home office/fourth bedroom and three bathrooms in the heart of Coburg. Unfolding over three levels, a contemporary layout features relaxing living area, opening onto a large terrace, and elevated open plan dining/kitchen zones displaying stone benches/breakfast bar, double pantries and quality stainless steel appliances. The three bedrooms have built-in-robes, including a master with ensuite and intimate balcony. Also features main bathroom, with shower, bath, stone vanity and toilet, plus ground-level bathroom/laundry. With split-system air conditioners, intercom, storage and premium undercover parking provided by automated tandem garage with direct home entry. Literally steps from Coburg Market, cosmopolitan shops, cafés, schools, parklands and all public transport.

Description:
Inner City Californian Bungalow
Boasting cul-de-sac serenity, original character and an inner city location that's second to none, this circa 1924 double fronted Californian Bungalow, comprising two charming bedrooms plus study/third bedroom, is just metres from Sydney Road shops, cafés and trams. Cherished by the same family for half a century, the freshly painted home features a wide block, manicured hedged gardens, high ceilings, polished Baltic pine floorboards and decorative rosette ceilings. Offering immediate comfort and excellent renovation/extension potential (subject to council approval), it currently comprises charming lounge, dining room, gas kitchen, central bathroom and sunroom opening to a large, private backyard enjoying a northerly aspect. Includes gas-heater, air-conditioner and full side drive with a double carport at the rear. Close proximity to Coburg Lake, Merri Creek trails/community market-gardens, schools, John Fawkner Hospital, trains and the CBD only moments away.

Description:
Exceptional Quality, Versatility and Urban Convenience
Modern low-maintenance perfection, this surprisingly spacious 3BR home delivers an environment of absolute quality and floorplan flexibility along with close proximity to cosmopolitan Coburg's renowned lifestyle attractions. Designed to take full advantage of its northerly aspect, the home's light-filled interior showcases an extra-large upstairs master bedroom with private dressing room and stylish ensuite, two additional bedrooms (one on each level) and two additional bathrooms (one on each level). Add to this a central study area/retreat and expansive open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a beautifully-appointed kitchen complete with stainless steel appliances and walk-in pantry. Other features include a full-size laundry and under-stair storeroom, ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, alarm, double glazing, tinted windows, solid hardwood floors, square-set ceilings and stone benchtops throughout. Step outside to discover an undercover entertaining deck and private north-facing back garden, plus the added advantage of a remote-control double garage via rear ROW. Walking distance to all public transport options and the open spaces of Bush Reserve, it's also close to local schools, Coburg's renowned shopping precinct, as well as Sydney Road cafes and restaurants.
Parking Available in Cramer St or High St
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
